almost to the point of the ridiculous. Few people realize that the thick
mirror finish is a result of years of touch ups and repolishing, and
that it was common practice to have your furniture recoated with French
polish any time it began to look shabby. French polish is not really
that durable, but is easy to repair, so in reality the majority of the
old pieces have already been refinished, in some cases yearly. In a lot
of cases, what we see as an original finish over here is just a sad
shadow of what it once was, like a over the hill movie star loaded up
with makeup, marquetry faded, veneers lifeless and pockmarked with
