antique furniture this side of the pond, and certainly that of the
Vicky stuff. I think this is down to expectation, this side of the
pond, dealers expect Vicky and semi-modern Edwardian stuff to be in
good condition and the lion's share of it to be original. And,
original not in 'as the day it left the factory' but used, most
